  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best Bank robbery movies?",
  "response": "There are many great bank robbery movies that capture the tension, excitement, and drama associated with heists. Here are some of the best:\n\n1. **Heat (1995)** - Directed by Michael Mann, this film features an incredible cast including Al Pacino and Robert De Niro, following a group of professional bank robbers and the dedicated detective determined to catch them.\n\n2. **Inside Man (2006)** - Directed by Spike Lee, this film stars Denzel Washington and Clive Owen in a clever heist that turns into a tense hostage situation, with unexpected twists and a thought-provoking ending.\n\n3. **The Town (2010)** - Directed by and starring Ben Affleck, this film is about a group of robbers in Charlestown, Massachusetts. It deftly combines action with emotional depth and character development.\n\n4. **Dog Day Afternoon (1975)** - Based on a true story, this Sidney Lumet classic stars Al Pacino as a desperate man trying to rob a bank to pay for his partner's surgery, resulting in a tense standoff with police.\n\n5. **Ocean\u2019s Eleven (2001)** - A stylish heist film directed by Steven Soderbergh, featuring an ensemble cast led by George Clooney. The movie combines humor with clever plotting as a group of thieves attempts to rob three Las Vegas casinos.\n\n6. **Bank Job (2008)** - Based on a real-life bank robbery that occurred in London, this film features Jason Statham and blends action with a fascinating conspiracy subplot.\n\n7. **The Bank Job (2008)** - This film, also starring Jason Statham, is a thrilling retelling of a 1971 bank robbery in London that uncovers secrets involving the British government and the criminal underworld.\n\n8. **Hell or High Water (2016)** - A modern Western about two brothers who rob banks to save their family ranch. The film explores themes of desperation and social injustice while delivering thrilling heist sequences.\n\n9. **The Great Heist (2004)** - A gripping film about a gang that pulls off a high-stakes robbery while facing off against law enforcement, blending action and drama.\n\n10. **Den of Thieves (2018)** - A thrilling crime drama that pits an elite unit of the LA County Sheriff's Department against a group of robbers planning a massive heist on the Federal Reserve.\n\nThese films not only showcase thrilling heists but also delve into complex characters and moral dilemmas, making them memorable contributions to the genre.",
